---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Foremost Machine, Inc. | Commercial Manufacturing Partner" description="We work exclusively with commercial accounts. Request access for quoting and production support.">
  <section class="section-shell">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-100">Commercial Manufacturing Support</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">Precision CNC support for commercial buyers, from prototype through repeat production.</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-300">Foremost Machine, Inc. helps procurement and engineering teams source tight-tolerance parts, reduce quoting friction, and keep recurring programs on schedule.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/request-access" class="rounded-md bg-brand-500 px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-white hover:bg-brand-700">Request Access</a>
          <a href="/capabilities" class="rounded-md border border-slate-600 px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-100 hover:border-slate-400">Review Capabilities</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Why teams choose Foremost</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-300">
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Tolerances:</span> Up to ±0.001" on critical dimensions (feature dependent).</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Materials:</span> Aluminum, stainless, tool steels, brass, and engineering plastics.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Quality:</span> First-article and in-process inspection reporting available.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Lead times:</span> Typical RFQ turnaround within 1–2 business days.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pt-0">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white">How engagement works</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="card"><h3 class="text-xl text-white">1) Qualification</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-300">Submit your business details, typical part profile, and expected order volume.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3 class="text-xl text-white">2) Technical review</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-300">Our team confirms manufacturability, lead-time expectations, and documentation needs.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3 class="text-xl text-white">3) Ongoing support</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-300">Approved accounts receive portal access for RFQs and customer documentation.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pt-0">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Quick FAQ</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-slate-300">
        <p><span class="font-semibold text-white">Who can open an account?</span> Commercial organizations with recurring part demand, engineering support needs, or production program requirements.</p>
        <p><span class="font-semibold text-white">How fast do you respond?</span> Most commercial access requests receive an initial response within 1 business day.</p>
        <p><span class="font-semibold text-white">Do you accept consumer or hobby projects?</span> No. We exclusively support B2B and industrial purchasing teams.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/request-access" class="rounded-md bg-brand-500 px-5 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-white hover:bg-brand-700">Start Account Request</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="rounded-md border border-slate-600 px-5 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-slate-100 hover:border-slate-400">Contact Sales</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
